gomodel:SYNGO_4708  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Immunohistochemical (IHC) staining on the P18-21 calyx of Held shows GIT1 and VLGUT1 co-localize (Figure S1a). Experimental description: Authors don't explicitly mention the species used in imaging assays at Figure S1, but all experiments are done in mice (from M&M). Abstract mentions mouse explicitly; \"Here, we demonstrate that presynaptic deletion of the two G protein-coupled receptor kinase-interacting proteins (GITs), GIT1 and GIT2, at the mouse calyx of Held leads to a large increase in AP-evoked release with no change in the readily releasable pool size.\"\n\nantibody:\nmonoclonal Mouse anti-GIT1, N39B/8, NeuroMab" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" ;
        dc:date           "2022-07-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_4708" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

